Police spokesperson Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said the possibility of more arrests could not be ruled out and appealed to anyone with information to come forward. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three suspects have been arrested for the kidnapping of Amy'Leigh de Jager. According to a statement released by the police, one man and two women aged between 27 and 50 were arrested before midnight on Wednesday. One suspect is allegedly known to Amy'Leigh's parents. "Members from the FCS Unit in Vanderbijlpark assisted by members from the FCS Unit in Vereeniging and Crime Intelligence members arrested two women aged 27 years and 40 years as well as a 50-year-old man at their homes in Vanderbijlpark. READ: Amy-Leigh de Jager found "The FCS Unit continued with the investigations and arrested the three suspects, one of whom (a female suspect) is known to the parents of Amy'Leigh", read the statement. Three suspects have been arrested in connection with the kidnapping of Amy'Leigh de Jager.Courtesy #DStv403 Amy'Leigh was taken from her mother's car by four men in an unmarked Toyota Fortuner at the Laerskool Kollegepark in Vanderbijlpark on Monday. The kidnappers demanded a R2-million ransom for her release. Police spokesperson Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said the possibility of more arrests could not be ruled out and appealed to anyone with information to come forward.